Credit Line: The Jefferson R. Burdick Collection, Gift of Jefferson R. Burdick
Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History: The United States and Canada, 1800–1900 A.D.
Description: Trade cards from the "Fishes and Fishing" series (N108), issued in a set of 25 cards in 1888 to promote Honest Long Cut Tobacco, manufactured by W. Duke Sons & Co. This set depicts the same images that are included in set N74 in a larger format.
